 View a FlexCard's Data JSON
 The Data JSON feature updates when you interact with the FlexCard, such as entering data in an input field or clicking an actionable item.
 cards, dataSource, Label, Params, recordId, Session, TestParams, theme, title, User are available objects that provide information on rendered cards, data source, custom labels, page parameters, Id, session variables, test parameters, FlexCard theme, name and user information.

View a FlexCard's Data JSON
The Data JSON panel updates when you interact with the FlexCard.
cards object displays information about rendered cards based on the data displayed and state conditions applied.
dataSource object displays the array of records returned from the data source.
Label object displays custom labels fetched for the FlexCard.
Params object displays Salesforce page parameters.
recordId object displays the Id of the FlexCard page as seen in the URL.

FlexCard Context Variables
View your FlexCard's context variables, such as logged-in user information.
